<section class="measure center lh-copy f5-ns f6 ph2 mv4" style="text-align: justify;">
<strong>"What's the danger?"</strong> Here are autogenerated DEM Shading rules for each advisory zone that allow for quickly adding avalanche danger, problems, and sun angle layers to CalTopo maps.
Reports sourced from <a class="no-underline fancy-link relative light-red" target="_blank" href="https://avalanche.org/">avalanche.org</a>.
</section>
<section class="measure center lh-copy f5-ns f6 ph2 mv4">
    <h2 class="bb b--moon-gray">Zones by Region</h2>
    {% for state in states %}
    {% if state.active %}
    <h3>{{ state.name }}</h3>
    <ul class="list pl3 f5 mt2">
        {% for zone in state.zones %}
        <li>
            <div style="clear: both;background-color: {{ zone.color }}" class="fl mr2 h1 w1"></div>
            <a class="no-underline fancy-link relative black-70 hover-light-red" href="{{ state.page }}.html#zone-{{ zone.slug }}">{{ zone.name }}</a>
            {% if zone.published and zone.color != "#939598" %}<span class="gray f7">{{ zone.published }}</span>{% endif %}
        </li>
        {% endfor %}
    </ul>
    {% endif %}
    {% endfor %}
</section>

